nd exploring new modes of interpretation, The Limits of Critique offers a fresh approach to the relationship between artistic works and the social world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aCriticismxMethodology. 0aCriticism. 0aHermeneutics. 0aSuspicion. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311069043940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226294179423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226294179.jpg  a978-3-11-069043-9  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles